<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[107,637,953,1741]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">
DIAGNOSIS: The following combination of characters distinguishes the species of subfamily Rhopalurusinae, New World 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1837" box="[466,570,1019,1043]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Buthidae</taxonomicName>
with accessory (supernumerary) denticles in median denticle rows of pedipalp chela fingers, from other buthid scorpions: chelicerae, movable finger with transverse row of granules; cheliceral fixed finger with dorsobasal setation; pedipalp femur, dorsal surface trichobothria with α-configuration, trichobothrium 
<emphasis box="[480,494,1252,1276]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">d</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[494,503,1263,1280]" fontSize="7" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">2</subScript>
situated on prolateral surface; pedipalp patella trichobothrium 
<emphasis box="[175,189,1318,1342]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">d</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[189,198,1329,1346]" fontSize="7" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">3</subScript>
situated retrolateral to dorsomedian carina; pedipalp chela, fixed and movable fingers, median denticle rows with pro- and retrolateral accessory (supernumerary) denticles; legs without tibial spurs; leg I telotarsus, prolateral pedal spur bifurcating (reduced in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1934" box="[107,241,1517,1541]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Physoctonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[107,241,1517,1541]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Physoctonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[107,637,953,1741]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">
INCLUDED TAXA: This New World buthid subfamily includes seven genera (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marx" authorityYear="1890" box="[438,575,1584,1608]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[438,575,1584,1608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Centruroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ischnotelson" authorityName=", Ischnotelson, Jaguajir" authorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Heteroctenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Heteroctenus</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[224,355,1617,1641]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Ischnotelson</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[372,476,1617,1641]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Lauren A. Esposito &amp; Humberto Y. Yamaguti &amp; Cláudio A. Souza &amp; Ricardo Pinto-Da-Rocha &amp; CLOSE Lorenzo Prendini Scorpion Systematics Research Group, 2017" authorityName="Lauren A. Esposito &amp; Humberto Y. Yamaguti &amp; Cláudio A. Souza &amp; Ricardo Pinto-Da-Rocha &amp; Lorenzo Prendini" authorityYear="2017" box="[489,573,1618,1641]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Jaguajir" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[489,573,1618,1641]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Jaguajir</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="8" pageNumber="8" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1934" box="[164,295,1650,1674]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Physoctonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[164,295,1650,1674]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Physoctonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1876" box="[308,431,1650,1674]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Rhopalurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[308,431,1650,1674]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Rhopalurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Troglorhopalurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Troglorhopalurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 108 described species, and three subspecies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="8" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[684,1214,228,715]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">DISTRIBUTION: Subfamily Rhopalurusinae is endemic to the New World and distributed from North America (the midwestern United States) throughout Central America and the Caribbean islands (Greater and Lesser Antilles) to centralnorthern South America and the Galapagos Islands.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[684,1214,228,715]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Bucherl's" box="[844,1031,460,484]" editor="W. Bucherl &amp; E. R. Buckley" firstAuthor="Bucherl's" journalOrPublisher="New York: Academic Press" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" pagination="317 - 348" part="3" refId="ref64808" refString="Bucherl, W. 1971. Classification, biology and venom extraction of scorpions. In W. Bucherl and E. R. Buckley (editors), Venomous animals and their venoms 3: 317 - 348. New York: Academic Press." title="Classification, biology and venom extraction of scorpions" type="journal article" volumeTitle="Venomous animals and their venoms" year="1971">Bücherl’s (1971)</bibRefCitation>
original name, Rhopalurinae, was a junior homonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Stunkard, 1937" authorityName="Stunkard" authorityYear="1937" family="Rhopaluridae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Orthonectida" rank="family">Rhopaluridae Stunkard, 1937</taxonomicName>
, derived from the orthonectid genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Girard, 1877" authorityName="Girard" authorityYear="1877" box="[835,1102,559,583]" family="Rhopaluridae" genus="Rhopalura" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Orthonectida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[835,948,559,583]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Rhopalura</emphasis>
Girard, 1877
</taxonomicName>
, and thus unavailable (
<bibRefCitation author="Fet and Lowe" box="[822,1042,592,616]" editor="V. Fet" firstAuthor="Fet" journalOrPublisher="New York: New York Entomological Society" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" pagination="54 - 286" refString="Fet, V., and G. Lowe. 2000. Family Buthidae C. L. Koch, 1837. In V. Fet, W. D. Sissom, G., Lowe, and M. E. Braunwalder, Catalog of the scorpions of the world (1758 - 1998): 54 - 286. New York: New York Entomological Society." title="Family Buthidae C. L. Koch, 1837" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="G., Lowe, and M. E" year="2000">Fet and Lowe, 2000</bibRefCitation>
). A 2003 ruling by the International Commision on Zoological Nomenclature amended Rhopalurinae to Rhopalurusinae 
<bibRefCitation author="Bucherl" box="[819,969,691,715]" editor="W. Bucherl" firstAuthor="Bucherl" journalOrPublisher="New York: Academic Press" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" pagination="317 - 348" part="3" refString="Bucherl, W. 1971. Classification, biology and venom extraction of scorpions. In W. Bucherl and E. R. Buckley (editors), Venomous animals and their venoms 3: 317 - 348. New York: Academic Press." title="Classification, biology and venom extraction of scorpions" type="journal article" volumeTitle="Venomous animals and their venoms" year="1971">Bücherl, 1971</bibRefCitation>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fet, V &amp; M. E. Petersen &amp; G. S. Slyusarev" box="[984,1164,691,715]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Zoological Nomenclature" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" pagination="23 - 25" part="60" refString="Fet, V., M. E. Petersen, and G. S. Slyusarev. 2003 b. Case 3151. Rhopalurusinae Bucherl, 1971 (Arachnida, Scorpiones, Buthidae): Proposed conservation as the correct spelling to remove homonymy with Rhopaluridae Stunkard, 1937 (Orthonectida). Bulletin of Zoological Nomenclature 60 (1): 23 - 25." title="Case 3151. Rhopalurusinae Bucherl, 1971 (Arachnida, Scorpiones, Buthidae): Proposed conservation as the correct spelling to remove homonymy with Rhopaluridae Stunkard, 1937 (Orthonectida)" type="journal article" year="2003" yearSuffix="b">Fet et al., 2003b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
